column5: Check this out. Can anyone explain this.https://i.imgur.com/qXBv2QX.gifv
Pike eats bass and choked on it. Both floated up and as ice thickened bass then pike frozen?   Art
I would think the pike died trying to eat that bass, floated upwards and ice formed around them
reasonably common to see pike or musky choke on a bass or sheephead
What Art and Rizzo said, I have see pike choking on Bluegill that went down the wrong way, that bass looks too big for that pike, but once they commit the problems happen?
Yep,it's the prey with spiny dorsal fins like bass that can choke a pike. I've seen a few dead pike with a walleye more than half their size sticking out of their mouth.
That would look cool on the wall!
